{"total_count":40,"incomplete_results":false,"items":[{"id":3402551858,"number":52558,"state":"closed","state_reason":"completed","locked":false,"title":"[BUG] No registered resource provider found for location 'westeurope' and API version '2025-03-01' for type 'publicIPAddresses'.","body":"### Library name and version

Azure.ResourceManager 1.13.0

### Describe the bug

We are using the SDK to delete different kinds of resources (VMs, KVs, disks, etc.):
```
await resource.DeleteAsync(WaitUntil.Started);
```
Today this call started to fail consistently with 400 Bad Request when deleting public IPs, network security groups and network interface cards. The error mentions a missing resource provider for a recent API version, but the resources were created via an ARM template using `2020-07-01`, while the SDK doesn't expose which version it uses.

### Expected behavior

The method call to succeed.

### Actual behavior

When deleting PIPs (same for NSGs and NICs) we get the following error message:
```
No registered resource provider found for location 'westeurope' and API version '2025-03-01' for type 'publicIPAddresses'. The supported api-versions are '2014-12-01-preview, 2015-05-01-preview, 2015-06-15, 2016-03-30, 2016-06-01, 2016-07-01, 2016-08-01, 2016-09-01, 2016-10-01, 2016-11-01, 2016-12-01, 2017-03-01, 2017-04-01, 2017-06-01, 2017-08-01, 2017-09-01, 2017-10-01, 2017-11-01, 2018-01-01, 2018-02-01, 2018-03-01, 2018-04-01, 2018-05-01, 2018-06-01, 2018-07-01, 2018-08-01, 2018-10-01, 2018-11-01, 2018-12-01, 2019-02-01, 2019-04-01, 2019-06-01, 2019-07-01, 2019-08-01, 2019-09-01, 2019-11-01, 2019-12-01, 2020-01-01, 2020-03-01, 2020-04-01, 2020-05-01, 2020-06-01, 2020-07-01, 2020-08-01, 2020-11-01, 2021-01-01, 2021-02-01, 2021-03-01, 2021-04-01, 2021-05-01, 2021-06-01, 2021-08-01, 2021-12-01, 2022-01-01, 2022-05-01, 2022-07-01, 2022-09-01, 2022-11-01, 2023-02-01, 2023-04-01, 2023-05-01, 2023-06-01, 2023-09-01, 2023-11-01, 2024-01-01, 2024-03-01, 2024-05-01, 2024-07-01, 2024-10-01, 2025-01-01'. The supported locations are 'westus, eastus, northeurope, westeurope, eastasia, southeastasia, northcentralus, southcentralus, centralus, eastus2, japaneast, japanwest, brazilsouth, australiaeast, australiasoutheast, centralindia, southindia, westindia, canadacentral, canadaeast, westcentralus, westus2, ukwest, uksouth, koreacentral, koreasouth, francecentral, australiacentral, southafricanorth, uaenorth, switzerlandnorth, germanywestcentral, norwayeast, westus3, jioindiawest, swedencentral, qatarcentral, polandcentral, italynorth, israelcentral, mexicocentral, spaincentral, newzealandnorth, indonesiacentral, austriaeast, chilecentral, malaysiawest'.
```

### Reproduction Steps

```
var resourceGroupName = "abc";
var resourcesPrefix = "abc";

var subscriptionId = "abc";
var tenantId = "abc";
var clientId = "abc";
var clientSecret = "abc";

var credentials = new ClientSecretCredential(
    tenantId,
    clientId,
    clientSecret);
var armClient = new ArmClient(credentials);

string resourceGroupId = $"/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}";
var rg = armClient.GetResourceGroupResource(ResourceIdentifier.Parse(resourceGroupId))?.Get()?.Value;
var resources = rg?.GetGenericResources($"substringof(\'{resourcesPrefix}\', name)", null, 20).ToList();

foreach (var resource in resources)
{
    try
    {
        await resource.DeleteAsync(WaitUntil.Started);
        Console.WriteLine($"Deleting resource: {resource.Id}");
    }
    catch (Exception ex)
    {
        Console.WriteLine($"Error processing resource {resource.Id}: {ex.Message}");
    }
}
